<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Z. Li &amp; X. Y. Ye" authorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Fargesia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fargesia viridis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Fargesia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.Z. Li &amp; X.Y. Ye resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. frigidis" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="frigidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. frigidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yi, 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. zayuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="zayuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. zayuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yi and 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. similaris" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="similaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. similaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hsueh &amp; Yi, but can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. frigidis" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="frigidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. frigidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by thinner and glabrous culm, more leaves on the ultimate branch, longer leaf sheath and large leaf blade, from 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. zayuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="zayuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. zayuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter and thinner culm, solid internode, more leaves on the ultimate branch and broader leaf blade, and from 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. similaris" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="similaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">F. similaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by solid internode, prominent sheath scar, setose culm sheath, glabrous petiole, more leaf number and larger leaf blade.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="materials_examined">
