<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Z. Li &amp; X. Y. Ye" authorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Fargesia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fargesia viridis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Fargesia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type locality, the Dulongjiang Town. It occurs along the stream and grows as pure bamboo forest or under the evergreen broadleaved forest at an elevation of 2600-2800 m alt.
</paragraph>
